---
const points = [
  "Distilled to what actually matters — no filler, no clickbait",
  "Written to flow like a story, not read like a list of bullets",
  "Every story keeps its source, so you can always dig deeper",
];
---

<section id="features" class="mx-auto w-full max-w-6xl px-4 sm:px-6">
  <div class="grid grid-cols-1 items-center gap-10 lg:grid-cols-2 lg:gap-16">
    <!-- copy -->
    <div class="flex max-w-xl flex-col gap-5">
      <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-widest text-tint-700 uppercase">Made to be heard</p>
      <h2 class="font-display text-3xl font-medium text-pretty text-ink-1 sm:text-4xl">
        Written for radio, not bullet points.
      </h2>
      <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed text-pretty text-ink-3">
        AI distils each story down to what actually matters, writes it into a
        script that flows, then reads it back in a clear, calm voice — the
        difference between skimming a feed and being told what happened.
      </p>
      <ul class="mt-1 flex flex-col gap-3">
        {
          points.map((p) => (
            <li class="flex items-start gap-2.5 text-[15px] text-ink-2">
              <svg width="22" height="22" viewBox="0 0 24 24" class="mt-px shrink-0 text-tint" fill="none">
                <path d="m7 13 3 3c1.5-5.5 6-9 6-9" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" />
              </svg>
              <span>{p}</span>
            </li>
          ))
        }
      </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- transcript card (decorative illustration of the script being written) -->
    <div class="relative" aria-hidden="true">
      <div class="hero-glow pointer-events-none absolute inset-x-0 -top-10 h-48" aria-hidden="true"></div>
      <div class="relative overflow-hidden rounded-2xl bg-elevated shadow-card ring-[0.5px] ring-line">
        <div class="flex items-center justify-between border-b border-line px-5 py-3">
          <span class="text-sm font-medium text-ink-2">Today's Briefing</span>
          <span class="text-xs font-medium text-ink-4">Friday · 4 topics · 7 min</span>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-5 p-5 sm:p-6">
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" width="24" height="24" class="size-6 shrink-0" />
            <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-1">
              Good morning. Here's the latest on the topics you follow.
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex gap-3">
            <span class="grid size-6 flex-none place-items-center rounded-full bg-surface-2">
              <svg width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" class="text-ink-3"><circle cx="12" cy="12" r="7.25" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" /><path stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.6" stroke-linecap="round" d="M4.75 12h14.5" /></svg>
            </span>
            <div class="flex min-w-0 flex-1 flex-col gap-2">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-1.5 text-[13px] text-ink-4">
                <span class="font-medium text-tint-700">Researching your topics</span>
                <span>· 4 topics · 11 sources</span>
              </div>
              <p class="text-[15px] leading-relaxed text-ink-2">
                First up in technology, the state of AI agents in 2026 — the big
                shift this year is from single prompts to long-running tasks.
                Then, in markets, why interest rates moved this week, and what it
                means for borrowers…
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 border-t border-line px-5 py-3.5">
          <button class="grid size-8 flex-none place-items-center rounded-full bg-palette-800 text-[12px] text-palette-50">▶</button>
          <div class="h-1.5 flex-1 overflow-hidden rounded-full bg-surface-2">
            <div class="h-full w-1/3 rounded-full bg-tint"></div>
          </div>
          <span class="text-[12px] tabular-nums text-ink-3">2:14 / 7:02</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
